-- Egypt to Announce Gas Importing Tender, Al Mal Reports
-- B y   N a d i n e   M a r r o u s h i
-- 2012-10-17T08:10:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-17/egypt-to-announce-gas-importing-tender-al-mal-reports.html
Egypt is preparing to invite
companies to tender for the import of between 1 and 1.5 billion
cubic meters of natural gas daily,  Al Mal  reported citing Osama Kamal, the Minister of Petroleum and  Mineral Resources .  Brochures setting out the details of the tender will be
available once the announcement is made either on Thursday or
Friday, the newspaper reported.  The winner will be responsible for importing gas and
supplying it to Egyptâ€™s network, while the ministry will handle
transporting the gas within the country, Kamal said.  Egypt plans to import gas to meet demand from power, cement
and steel plants, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
